1. Docker run command for nextcloud AIO:
sudo docker run \
  --init \
  --sig-proxy=false \
  --name nextcloud-aio-mastercontainer \
  --restart always \
  --publish 8080:8080 \
  --publish 11000:11000 \
  --volume nextcloud_aio_mastercontainer:/mnt/docker-aio-config \
  --volume /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock:ro \
  -e NEXTCLOUD_DATADIR="/mnt/kingston/nextcloud-data" \
  -e APACHE_PORT=11000 \
  -e APACHE_IP_BINDING=0.0.0.0 \
  -e SKIP_DOMAIN_VALIDATION=true \
  ghcr.io/nextcloud-releases/all-in-one:latest


Publishes web interface on 8080 and 11000 for nginx proxy manager. Stores data in NEXTCLOUD_DATADIR.

2. Splits large uploads into chunks to stop cloudflare from denying upload
sudo docker exec --user www-data nextcloud-aio-nextcloud php occ config:app:set files max_chunk_size --value 10485760
